    <h2>Learn About My School</h2>
    <p>In this unit, we will learn how to talk about school in English. You will learn vocabulary related to school subjects, teachers, classrooms, and activities. Let's explore some important words and phrases!</p>

    <h3>Key Vocabulary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>School</strong> - A place where you learn.</li>
      <li><strong>Classroom</strong> - A room in the school where lessons take place.</li>
      <li><strong>Teacher</strong> - A person who teaches students.</li>
      <li><strong>Student</strong> - A person who is learning in a school.</li>
      <li><strong>Subject</strong> - A topic you study in school (e.g., Maths, Science, History).</li>
      <li><strong>Lesson</strong> - A period of teaching in a subject.</li>
      <li><strong>Homework</strong> - Assignments given by the teacher to be completed at home.</li>
      <li><strong>Library</strong> - A room with books for reading and studying.</li>
      <li><strong>Playground</strong> - An outdoor area where students play during breaks.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Common Expressions for Talking About School</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>What’s your favorite subject?</strong> - A question about someone’s preferred subject.</li>
      <li><strong>I have English class today.</strong> - A sentence about a specific class.</li>
      <li><strong>My teacher is very nice.</strong> - Describing a teacher.</li>
      <li><strong>Do you like Maths?</strong> - Asking about a subject.</li>
      <li><strong>I need to do my homework.</strong> - Talking about assignments.</li>
      <li><strong>We have a test tomorrow.</strong> - Talking about exams.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Grammar Focus</h3>
    <p>In this unit, we will focus on the present simple tense to talk about daily activities and routines. Here are some examples:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>I study</strong> English every day. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>She teaches</strong> History. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>They play</strong> basketball in the playground. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>Do you have</strong> Maths today? (question)</li>
      <li><strong>Yes, I do.</strong> (positive response)</li>
      <li><strong>No, I don’t.</strong> (negative response)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Extra Practice</h3>
